The paper deals with the problem of knowledge graph embedding, which is a subfield of artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and machine learning (cs.LG). The proposed method involves the use of recurrent neural networks (RNNs), which are commonly used in natural language processing (cs.CL) and sequential data analysis (cs.DB). The paper also discusses entity alignment and KG completion, which are tasks related to information retrieval (cs.IR).
